---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Callout from '../components/Callout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Get Help"
  description="Step-by-step support after a suspected scam, including trusted reporting links and recovery actions."
  canonicalPath="/get-help"
  intro="If something feels wrong, pause. You can take this one step at a time."
>
  <section class="section-space pb-0 space-y-6">
    <Callout title="First, take a breath" type="tip">
      <p class="m-0">Scammers rely on urgency. Slowing down is a strong and effective response.</p>
    </Callout>

    <article class="panel p-8 prose">
      <h2>Immediate steps</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Stop contact with the suspected scammer.</li>
        <li>Call your bank, card issuer, or payment service right away.</li>
        <li>Change passwords for email, banking, and key accounts from a trusted device.</li>
        <li>Save evidence: screenshots, receipts, phone numbers, usernames, and messages.</li>
        <li>Talk to someone you trust before sending any more money.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Report the scam</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Federal Trade Commission (FTC):
          <a href="https://reportfraud.ftc.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">reportfraud.ftc.gov</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          FBI Internet Crime Complaint Center (IC3):
          <a href="https://www.ic3.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">ic3.gov</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Support matters</h2>
      <p>
        You are not alone, and this is not your fault. Sharing what happened with a trusted person can help you make clear decisions and avoid additional loss.
      </p>

      <h2>Local support contacts</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Eldercare Locator (U.S. Administration for Community Living):
          <a href="https://eldercare.acl.gov/home" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">1-800-677-1116</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          211 community support line (United Way and local partners): Call 211 or visit
          <a href="https://www.211.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">211.org</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
